HEADWORD: Ekaboron
<hw>Ek"a*bo"ron</hw> <pr>(-b⟦omac⟧"r⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[G., fr. Skr. <ets>⟦emac⟧ka</ets> one + G. <ets>bor</ets>,
<ets>boron</ets>, E. <ets>boron</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The name given by Mendelejeff in accordance with the periodic law,
and by prediction, to a hypothetical element then unknown, but since
discovered and named <altname>scandium</altname>; -- so called because
it was a missing analogue of the boron group. See
<er>Scandium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ekaluminium</ent>⟦br⟧
